Paul Tremblay became a member of the Read Alphabet group in late 
September, 2007.  At that time, he had recently moved to Louisville, 
Kentucky near where I live.  We never met in person.  He was very 
enthusiastic about QS and designed the Thoth font soon after becoming a 
member.  I provided a modest amount of assistance in reviewing his 
initial font design and making some suggestions to him.

Paul set up the daily news in QS, which took AP news releases and 
transliterated them into QS.  It was useful in providing timely QS 
readings for reading practice.  When he was unable to continue doing 
that, the news disappeared.  It would be nice to see it come back as 
lack of reading material is one of the major stumbling blocks which keep 
people from increasing their reading speed.

In December, 2007, he was working on a QS dictionary and a number of 
posts were sent between Paul and Benct Philip Jonsson who was also 
working on a dictionary proposal at that time.

He asked for someone to take over the news on 1/14/08 because he did not 
have the time to continue it.  His last post was only 2 days later.  
Since then we have not heard from him.  He is not currently a member of 
the group as far as I am aware.

There is no particular reason to view the letter names he used as canonical.

Regards,


Paige



